# HippoTail — Skeptic Report

Maintained by: Skeptic  
Last updated: YYYY-MM-DD

This document records critiques of hypotheses, methods, and interpretations.

The goal is to identify:

• confounds  
• alternative explanations  
• weaknesses in reasoning  

---

# Current Concerns

### Electrode Coverage Bias

Tail electrodes are sparse in many datasets.

Possible effect

Apparent connectivity differences may reflect sampling bias.

---

### Distance Effects

Evoked potentials attenuate with distance.

Possible effect

Connectivity strength may reflect geometry rather than true connectivity.

---

### White Matter Proximity

Tail electrodes may be close to white matter tracts.

Possible effect

Observed responses may represent tract stimulation rather than hippocampal gray matter connectivity.

---

# Suggested Tests

1. Control for Euclidean distance.
2. Test robustness across patients.
3. Exclude contacts near white matter tracts.

---

# Alternative Hypotheses

Connectivity differences may be explained by:

• distance  
• electrode placement bias  
• recording artifacts
